<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Impose2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Impose,</orth> vb. 1) to lay on, as a burden, office, order, or penalty: <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.204" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.165" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 165</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.250" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 250</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 3, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 26</bibl>. With <cit><quote>on:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 3, 40</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.130" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.850" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 850</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.157" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 157</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.147" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 147</bibl>.<lb />2) to enjoin, to oblige by command: <cit><quote>i. me to what penance your invention can lay upon my sin,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.282" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 282</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>